cs.HC, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.SI 

The paper discusses data exploration and visualization systems, which are typically studied in the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also focuses on large dynamic sets of data, which are commonly studied in the Database (cs.DB) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The proposed model is built on a tree-based structure, which is a common data structure studied in the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a web-based prototype tool, which falls under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
